Title : Change Italy
Text : '''Change Italy''' (''Cambia l'Italia'') was a [[social democracy|social-democratic]] faction within the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] (PD),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2011-10-29/bersaniani-rottamatori-renzi-ecco-133946_PRN.shtml|title=Dai bersaniani ai rottamatori di Renzi: - In casa dei democratici si preferisce - Il Sole 24 ORE|website=www.ilsole24ore.com|accessdate=10 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blitzquotidiano.it/politica-italiana/partito-democratico-correnti-renzi-zingaretti-994101/|title=Il Pd delle 17 correnti: Renzi e Zingaretti, D'Alema e Veltroni futuri - Blitz quotidiano|date=24 October 2011|publisher=|accessdate=10 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://xvileg.senatoripd.it/dettaglio/70911/# |title=Archived copy |access-date=2016-02-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160224063304/http://xvileg.senatoripd.it/dettaglio/70911/# |archive-date=2016-02-24 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> a [[list of political parties in Italy|political party in Italy]].

Its leader, [[Ignazio Marino]], ran in the [[2009 Democratic Party (Italy) leadership election|2009 party's leadership election]] on a platform named "Live the PD, change Italy",<ref>[http://archiviostorico.unita.it/cgi-bin/highlightPdf.cgi?t=ebook&file=/edizioni/20090905/pdf/NAZ/pages/20090905_35_05PUB35A.pdf&query=]{{dead link|date=November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.pdsicilia.it/writable/pdf/file_38.pdf# |title=Archived copy |access-date=2016-02-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303172016/http://www.pdsicilia.it/writable/pdf/file_38.pdf# |archive-date=2016-03-03 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> gaining 12.5% of the vote and losing to [[Pier Luigi Bersani]]. The faction was structured in 2010,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://archive.partitodemocratico.it/doc/93528/pd-marino-la-politica-riparta-dalle-idee-per-modernizzare-il-paese-per-questo-nascecambia-litalia.htm# |title=Archived copy |access-date=2016-02-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160308045505/http://archive.partitodemocratico.it/doc/93528/pd-marino-la-politica-riparta-dalle-idee-per-modernizzare-il-paese-per-questo-nascecambia-litalia.htm# |archive-date=2016-03-08 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=di luca filippetti |url=http://www.orvietonews.it/politica/2010/02/06/parte-da-orvieto-cambia-l-italia-laboratorio-di-idee-promosso-da-ignazio-marino-pd-23569.html#.U1-eBqLNnsk |title=Parte da Orvieto "Cambia l'Italia" laboratorio di idee promosso da Ignazio Marino (PD) |publisher=Orvietonews.it |language=Italian |date=2000-12-14 |accessdate=2014-04-29}}</ref> but soon after it ceased to exist. In 2013 Marino was elected [[Mayor of Rome]] and left national politics.

